way in which I can understand

00:42:54.364 --> 00:42:57.547
your question is that you see
some kind of divergence,

00:42:57.547 --> 00:42:58.929
some sort of break.
 

00:42:58.929 --> 00:43:02.657
On the one hand this kind of
invective, the mode of the

00:43:02.657 --> 00:43:05.902
invective in Dante when talking
about Peter, St.

00:43:05.902 --> 00:43:08.320
Peter in Paradiso XXVII.
 

00:43:08.320 --> 00:43:13.664
I mean, he doesn't--he looks
back after the examination on

00:43:13.664 --> 00:43:16.534
faith,
he looks back and he starts

00:43:16.534 --> 00:43:20.210
attacking what he takes to be
the use of patience,

00:43:20.210 --> 00:43:22.474
my place;
remember that,

00:43:22.474 --> 00:43:28.320
an incredibly moral voice that
rises right at the very end.

00:43:28.320 --> 00:43:32.103
You seem to be worried about
the fact that Dante seems to be

00:43:32.103 --> 00:43:34.806
so moral and--
when it comes about the popes

00:43:34.806 --> 00:43:37.349
and then becomes mystical all of
a sudden,

00:43:37.349 --> 00:43:38.920
is that really one of your
concerns?

00:43:38.920 --> 00:43:40.907
It could be,
it could become one of your

00:43:40.907 --> 00:43:43.050
concerns in asking this question
about--

00:43:43.050 --> 00:43:46.420
at the end of Paradise
XXXIII he talks about Bernard

00:43:46.420 --> 00:43:49.849
such a mystic and yet all over
he has been talking about the

00:43:49.849 --> 00:43:50.489
papacy.
 

00:43:50.489 --> 00:43:55.567
If you were interested in that
I would say there is no

00:43:55.567 --> 00:44:01.601
divergence in Dante between the
prophetic voice and the mystical

00:44:01.601 --> 00:44:02.559
voice.
 

00:44:02.559 --> 00:44:08.610
That is something--even those
who read the Bible would go on

00:44:08.610 --> 00:44:13.329
saying, well,
the prophets were visionaries.

00:44:13.329 --> 00:44:15.998
In a way it's true but in a way
it's not true,

00:44:15.998 --> 00:44:19.025
the prophets were not
visionaries, the prophets were

00:44:19.025 --> 00:44:20.389
readers of history.
 

00:44:20.389 --> 00:44:24.900
They don't need to have Daniel
give an interpretation;

00:44:24.900 --> 00:44:28.043
Ezekiel has visions,
but Isaiah doesn't have visions

00:44:28.043 --> 00:44:30.199
so it's--you see what I'm
saying?

00:44:30.199 --> 00:44:33.706
There is no clear-cut
distinction between the

00:44:33.706 --> 00:44:37.929
prophetic and the mystical,
certainly not in Dante.

00:44:37.929 --> 00:44:41.889
The two belong together so
that's--I don't know that I'm

00:44:41.889 --> 00:44:46.208
answering your concerns but I
overheard a number of let's say

00:44:46.208 --> 00:44:48.440
rumblings in your question.
 

00:44:48.440 --> 00:44:50.139
I'm trying to take care of them.
 

00:44:50.139 --> 00:44:53.860
Student:  Is it a
reconciliation with the papacy?

00:44:53.860 --> 00:44:57.420
Prof: No,
not in the sense--no.

00:44:57.420 --> 00:45:03.105
To talk about--even Bernard is
someone who understands how

00:45:03.105 --> 00:45:09.389
waylaying the office can be and
he was obviously writing because

00:45:09.389 --> 00:45:14.875
he must be aware of what has
been happening and what was

00:45:14.875 --> 00:45:17.170
likely to happen.
 

00:45:17.170 --> 00:45:20.934
You don't have to become a
chronicler or an historian to do

00:45:20.934 --> 00:45:23.800
that;
you can imagine this can happen.

00:45:23.800 --> 00:45:26.139
No, there is not that.
 

00:45:26.139 --> 00:45:31.847
I think that's Dante's judgment
about history is always very

00:45:31.847 --> 00:45:34.460
clear until the very end.
 

00:45:34.460 --> 00:45:41.230
History needs a reform and of
course he would say,

00:45:41.230 --> 00:45:44.608
because he's one who believes
in the sacramentality and

00:45:44.608 --> 00:45:48.844
presence of the self,
how the self is crucial--before

00:45:48.844 --> 00:45:53.873
I start talking about how the
world needs reforming let me

00:45:53.873 --> 00:45:55.550
just begin here.
 

00:45:55.550 --> 00:46:00.099
That would be an obvious way to
say it,

00:46:00.099 --> 00:46:03.400
so I call it the language of
presence in him,

00:46:03.400 --> 00:46:07.228
a sense of, I am present to my
own self and therefore I have

00:46:07.228 --> 00:46:10.800
responsibilities toward my own
self before I became--

00:46:10.800 --> 00:46:16.320
I started using the megaphones
and let's reform the world.

00:46:16.320 --> 00:46:20.387
That probably--if there were
ever to come and Dante's not a

00:46:20.387 --> 00:46:23.365
utopian thinker,
it would come only because so

00:46:23.365 --> 00:46:27.018
many people of good will,
men and women of good will,

00:46:27.018 --> 00:46:30.764
his saints,
his blessed--the blessed souls

00:46:30.764 --> 00:46:35.670
that he meets are willing to do
something about that.

00:46:35.670 --> 00:46:39.012
No, no reconciliation,
not a sense of finally things

00:46:39.012 --> 00:46:41.829
will be becoming together,
I don't think.

00:46:41.829 --> 00:46:44.250
Actually I hold onto that.
 

00:46:54.050 --> 00:46:58.251
Student:  Just thinking
more about desire and wealth and

00:46:58.251 --> 00:47:01.978
the fact that the will is what
loves and the will always

00:47:01.978 --> 00:47:05.400
contains some element of lack,
or desire it seems,

00:47:05.400 --> 00:47:08.391
so even if it can attain
plentitude it still seems that

00:47:08.391 --> 00:47:12.099
Dante in talking so much about
